<paragraph blockId="9.[133,1155,1234,1719]" pageId="9" pageNumber="20">
Male. Head as 
<figureCitation box="[352,432,1235,1259]" captionStart="Figs 33–35" captionStartId="8.[133,170,1686,1705]" captionTargetBox="[142,1153,1015,1656]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 33–35. Megaselia kajaaniensis n. sp. male: 33 – head; 34–35 – scutellum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252163" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252163/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="20">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
, with dense but very fine microtrichia. Cheek with 5 bristles and jowl with two that are longer and more robust. Postpedicels without SPS vesicles. Palps pale brown or darker, with 6 bristles, a dozen hairs and small circular pits on their outer faces. Labrum pale and small. Labella pale and lacking short spinules below. Thorax brown. Three notopleural bristles and no cleft in front of these. Mesopleuron with 5–7 hairs and a bristle. Scutellum with an anterior pair of hairs, a posterior pair of bristles and a pair of small hairs (
<figureCitation box="[141,266,1418,1443]" captionStart="Figs 33–35" captionStartId="8.[133,170,1686,1705]" captionTargetBox="[142,1153,1015,1656]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 33–35. Megaselia kajaaniensis n. sp. male: 33 – head; 34–35 – scutellum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252163" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252163/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="20">Figs 34–35</figureCitation>
). Abdominal tergites brown with numerous hairs that are longest at the rear of 
<specimenCode box="[1117,1150,1419,1443]" collectionCode="T" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="9" pageNumber="20">T6</specimenCode>
. Venter brown and with hairs on segments 3–6. Hypopygium as 
<figureCitation box="[836,961,1449,1473]" captionStart="Figs 36–41" captionStartId="9.[133,170,1160,1179]" captionTargetBox="[137,1153,258,1131]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 36–41. Megaselia kajaaniensis n. sp. male: 36–37 – hypopygium; 38 – front tarsus, 39 – basitarsus of front tarsus; 40 – hind femur; 41 – right wing of paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252167/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="20">Figs 36–37</figureCitation>
. Middle and hind legs brown. Front legs, apart from brown bases to coxae, yellow. Fore tarsus as 
<figureCitation box="[1013,1093,1480,1504]" captionStart="Figs 36–41" captionStartId="9.[133,170,1160,1179]" captionTargetBox="[137,1153,258,1131]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 36–41. Megaselia kajaaniensis n. sp. male: 36–37 – hypopygium; 38 – front tarsus, 39 – basitarsus of front tarsus; 40 – hind femur; 41 – right wing of paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252167/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="20">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
, with the basitarsus as 
<figureCitation box="[318,398,1510,1535]" captionStart="Figs 36–41" captionStartId="9.[133,170,1160,1179]" captionTargetBox="[137,1153,258,1131]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 36–41. Megaselia kajaaniensis n. sp. male: 36–37 – hypopygium; 38 – front tarsus, 39 – basitarsus of front tarsus; 40 – hind femur; 41 – right wing of paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252167/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="20">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
. Dorsal hair palisade of mid tibia extends about 0.65 times its length. Hind femur as 
<figureCitation box="[299,380,1541,1565]" captionStart="Figs 36–41" captionStartId="9.[133,170,1160,1179]" captionTargetBox="[137,1153,258,1131]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 36–41. Megaselia kajaaniensis n. sp. male: 36–37 – hypopygium; 38 – front tarsus, 39 – basitarsus of front tarsus; 40 – hind femur; 41 – right wing of paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252167/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="20">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
. Hind tibia with a dozen moderately differentiated posterodorsal hairs, without anterodorsals, and spinules of apical combs simple. Wings 
<quantity box="[887,1019,1572,1596]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="9" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="1.45" valueMax="1.6" valueMin="1.3">1.3–1.6 mm</quantity>
long. Right wing of 
<typeStatus box="[230,322,1603,1627]" pageId="9" pageNumber="20">paratype</typeStatus>
as 
<figureCitation box="[365,445,1603,1627]" captionStart="Figs 36–41" captionStartId="9.[133,170,1160,1179]" captionTargetBox="[137,1153,258,1131]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 36–41. Megaselia kajaaniensis n. sp. male: 36–37 – hypopygium; 38 – front tarsus, 39 – basitarsus of front tarsus; 40 – hind femur; 41 – right wing of paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252167/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="20">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
but left wing lacks the cross vein linking veins 4 and 5 (as in normal phorid wings). Vein 7 not evident. Costal index 0.45–0.53. Costal ratios 3.5–4.2: 1.3– 1.4: 1. Costal cilia (of section 3) 
<quantity box="[516,614,1664,1688]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.10 mm</quantity>
long. No hair at base of vein 3. With 3 axillary bristles, the outer being 
<quantity box="[390,485,1695,1719]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="9" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="0.12">0.12 mm</quantity>
long. Sc not reaching 
<specimenCode box="[725,758,1695,1719]" collectionCode="R" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="9" pageNumber="20">R1</specimenCode>
. Haltere brown.
</paragraph>
